This place is called flavors and I'm telling ya, there's more flavours here than a Gelato Messina. Walking in to this set up, positioned nicely in Downtown Manhattan, you'll find 4 serving stations operated by what can only be described as efficient legends. Taking a bit of a gamble, I decided to splurge a little bit and order the 'Power BLT.'  Deadset, you've never seen a better sammich.  This piece of machinery for your turret will change your perception on life in general. Packed with all the gear that a tourist needs and topped off with lashings of avo that would make a Bondi cafe owner blush.  Bugger paying an extra $3 for half an avo in the Eastern suburbs of Sydney! The lads at Flavors will make sure your sammich is avo'd up to the extreme. Wash it all down with a freshly squeezed juice from an orange while sitting in seats that give a real cushioning for your blurter!  Flavors! If you're a mover and shaker in the Financial District, the NASDAQ is down and you need something to give you that edge, look no further. It's one thing to taste flavours, it's another to be in Flavor Country!

"Manhattan's Favorite Fast Casual Restaurant" says it all.  It's not our favorite restaurant.  It's not even our favorite casual restaurant.  It exists for the days when you want a paper bag with edible contents thrown in your direction for a reasonable price faster than the amount of time it takes you to come up with better lunch plans.  Much like your local high school, it can leave a lot to be desired, but after a while it becomes familiar, if not endearing.  If you can stand the occasional cheese steak soup and high pressure salad ordering, Flavors is a pretty good option in the area.

Flavors is one of my favorite places to grab a quick lunch when I'm downtown. The food here is really good, and service is lightning quick. Its a good idea to know what you want before you go in as standing around might get you run over. I especially like their sandwiches.

After having seen this place too many times to count, finally made my way in. Only had a sandwich this go 'round, but they had quite a variety of offerings and I'd say were more varied in their selection than lots I've seen around here. I had some sort of Jamaican jerk chicken sandwich, which was mighty tasty.  They are really quick to move you through. The only thing which was a little frustrating to the customer is that the sandwiches aren't listed on a menu board -- so you have to sort of worm your way through other patrons waiting/looking to see what your options are (and squeeze further up if you want to read what's *in* the sandwich, etc. etc.). That aside, offerings were great, sandwich delivered, and definitely want to squeeze through the crowd some more to try out some of the yummy looking selections I didn't manage to see before placing my order! I once tried their healthier wrap options. Hmmmm. Surprise surprise, not as good as the all-out options! It was decent, but if I was going for a healthier option, would vote for Subway. Tastes decent and significantly lower on the sticker price.
